1
00:00:00,268 --> 00:00:01,535
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,535 --> 00:00:02,768
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:05,168 --> 00:00:06,268
(Grandpa)

4
00:00:06,268 --> 00:00:07,301
(Grandpa)

5
00:00:07,668 --> 00:00:08,968
(Episode 2)

6
00:00:09,852 --> 00:00:11,752
- Grandpa.
- So you're still alive.

7
00:00:12,293 --> 00:00:15,260
I thought you were dead
since you never called.

8
00:00:16,456 --> 00:00:18,233
What did you send me earlier?

9
00:00:18,406 --> 00:00:20,739
Your grandfather is dying.

10
00:00:22,092 --> 00:00:23,392
It's stage four lung cancer.

11
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:27,099
Are you listening to me?

12
00:00:29,759 --> 00:00:32,000
Grandpa, you're joking, right?

13
00:00:32,513 --> 00:00:34,679
You're angry because I've been distant,
aren't you?

14
00:00:35,632 --> 00:00:36,632
You brat.

15
00:00:37,259 --> 00:00:40,126
If you don't believe me,
check with Mr. Seo.

16
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:43,033
Keep your promise.

17
00:00:43,639 --> 00:00:45,506
The one you made
to repay your grandfather.

18
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:48,546
- Grandpa.
- Wrap things up and come back right away.

19
00:00:49,190 --> 00:00:52,400
If you come after I'm dead,
it'll all be pointless.

20
00:00:52,953 --> 00:00:55,286
How are you supposed to repay a dead man?

21
00:01:25,945 --> 00:01:27,945
You look just like Assistant Manager Han.

22
00:01:29,340 --> 00:01:31,173
So you're Gyeol?

23
00:01:33,339 --> 00:01:36,806
I'm the president
of your father's company.

24
00:01:39,512 --> 00:01:40,512
How old are you?

25
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,340
He can't speak.

26
00:01:44,719 --> 00:01:45,719
Sorry?

27
00:01:46,383 --> 00:01:48,566
It's probably because he saw what happened
to his dad right in front of him.

28
00:01:49,383 --> 00:01:51,566
Since that day, he hasn't said a word.

29
00:01:51,746 --> 00:01:52,746
Excuse me.

30
00:01:53,619 --> 00:01:54,686
Just a moment, please.

31
00:02:05,546 --> 00:02:09,046
Your father was truly a great man.

32
00:02:10,826 --> 00:02:11,859
He'll be watching...

33
00:02:13,025 --> 00:02:14,959
over you from above.

34
00:02:16,546 --> 00:02:17,546
So...

35
00:02:18,552 --> 00:02:19,552
My goodness...

36
00:02:20,153 --> 00:02:23,720
How could he rest in peace
with this child on his mind?

37
00:02:25,519 --> 00:02:26,719
What happened?

38
00:02:27,123 --> 00:02:29,793
His uncle said he would take him in.

39
00:02:29,979 --> 00:02:30,979
You know how it goes.

40
00:02:31,285 --> 00:02:33,085
He probably took
all the insurance money...

41
00:02:33,586 --> 00:02:35,652
and company support, and then disappeared.

42
00:02:36,959 --> 00:02:39,559
It's been over six months since he came,
but he still has mutism.

43
00:02:39,806 --> 00:02:41,639
So he can't even go to school.

44
00:02:41,785 --> 00:02:42,785
What?

45
00:02:45,003 --> 00:02:46,150
(Hanbit Orphanage)

46
00:02:58,519 --> 00:03:01,186
This is my house.

47
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:04,440
Starting today,
it's your home too, Gyeol.

48
00:03:06,479 --> 00:03:08,546
This is your grandmother.

49
00:03:09,792 --> 00:03:12,059
You've been through a lot.
Welcome, sweetheart.

50
00:03:14,710 --> 00:03:15,731
What are you doing?

51
00:03:15,859 --> 00:03:17,692
Sorry? Yes, Father.

52
00:03:18,152 --> 00:03:20,133
Hello. Welcome.

53
00:03:20,483 --> 00:03:21,778
I'm your dad.

54
00:03:21,780 --> 00:03:24,080
She'll be your mom from now on.

55
00:03:25,793 --> 00:03:28,160
Min Ho, this is your little brother.

56
00:03:28,826 --> 00:03:31,460
Get along well, okay?

57
00:03:32,893 --> 00:03:35,443
No! I don't want a little brother!

58
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,833
I don't want one!

59
00:03:38,017 --> 00:03:39,700
Hey! When your grandpa speaks,

60
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:41,266
you should say, "Yes, sir."

61
00:03:43,879 --> 00:03:46,312
Hey, you can't talk?

62
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:47,993
Why aren't you saying anything?

63
00:03:50,459 --> 00:03:51,993
My gosh. Father.

64
00:03:52,806 --> 00:03:54,172
Is he disabled?

65
00:03:55,133 --> 00:03:57,700
I mean, adopting him so suddenly
is one thing,

66
00:03:57,830 --> 00:03:59,666
but asking us to raise a child
who can't even speak...

67
00:03:59,845 --> 00:04:00,845
Enough!

68
00:04:01,386 --> 00:04:03,753
I'm sorry. She spoke out of turn.

69
00:04:04,693 --> 00:04:05,726
Apologize to him.

70
00:04:06,879 --> 00:04:10,633
Come on, let's unpack first.

71
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:31,733
Go ahead, cry.

72
00:04:32,819 --> 00:04:34,419
Cry out loud as much as you want.

73
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:36,947
If you keep it all inside,

74
00:04:37,926 --> 00:04:39,959
it'll harden in your heart.

75
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,666
Dad...

76
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:51,053
Gyeol...

77
00:04:51,945 --> 00:04:56,779
Dad!

78
00:04:59,139 --> 00:05:00,639
Dad!

79
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:03,613
Dad!

80
00:05:03,733 --> 00:05:07,633
My goodness, it seems like his heart
has finally opened up.

81
00:05:07,633 --> 00:05:09,166
Dad.

82
00:05:14,013 --> 00:05:15,079
Dad.

83
00:05:16,046 --> 00:05:17,879
Dad.

84
00:05:22,633 --> 00:05:25,966
Keep the promise you made.

85
00:05:27,659 --> 00:05:29,093
Grandpa!

86
00:05:37,546 --> 00:05:38,700
Is that true?

87
00:05:38,873 --> 00:05:41,173
Kangsu Construction
is really going to invest in us?

88
00:05:43,396 --> 00:05:45,333
I never thought they'd decide...

89
00:05:45,492 --> 00:05:47,492
right after the first meeting.

90
00:05:48,126 --> 00:05:49,259
What are the terms?

91
00:05:49,992 --> 00:05:51,759
An initial investment of 500,000 dollars.

92
00:05:51,761 --> 00:05:53,433
500,000 dollars?

93
00:05:55,352 --> 00:05:57,490
- Hey, Cho Eun Ae.
- Yes, Ji Hun.

94
00:06:02,085 --> 00:06:04,519
Go out with me, Eun Ae.

95
00:06:06,464 --> 00:06:07,464
What?

96
00:06:07,466 --> 00:06:09,000
I pretended not to notice your feelings...

97
00:06:10,613 --> 00:06:12,413
because we hadn't properly established
ourselves yet.

98
00:06:13,519 --> 00:06:15,886
I didn't have the time
to think about dating.

99
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:18,666
But now that we've secured
proper investment,

100
00:06:19,427 --> 00:06:20,927
I'm mustering the courage
to confess my feelings for you.

101
00:06:22,690 --> 00:06:24,633
From now on, I'll handle...

102
00:06:24,846 --> 00:06:26,179
all the complicated investment matters.

103
00:06:28,113 --> 00:06:30,146
You just focus on development, Eun Ae.

104
00:06:31,033 --> 00:06:32,033
You trust me, right?

105
00:06:38,157 --> 00:06:40,097
(Lucky Joy Tech Intellectual Property
and Acquisition Agreement)

106
00:06:41,033 --> 00:06:44,233
(Lucky Joy Tech Intellectual Property
and Acquisition Agreement)

107
00:06:45,146 --> 00:06:48,400
So Ji Hun grabbed your cheeks like this...

108
00:06:48,926 --> 00:06:50,726
My goodness!

109
00:06:51,923 --> 00:06:53,700
I seriously had no idea he liked me,

110
00:06:53,860 --> 00:06:56,426
not even in my dreams.

111
00:06:56,566 --> 00:06:58,123
You're so dense.

112
00:06:58,216 --> 00:06:59,996
No wonder you were
a clueless engineering nerd.

113
00:07:00,063 --> 00:07:01,556
Who said that?

114
00:07:01,606 --> 00:07:04,711
You said you'd be
the "engineering goddess"...

115
00:07:04,713 --> 00:07:06,833
and land a campus boyfriend. What a joke.

116
00:07:07,070 --> 00:07:09,966
Whatever. What matters is the present.

117
00:07:10,113 --> 00:07:11,113
Agreed.

118
00:07:11,893 --> 00:07:13,493
Tell me more in detail.

119
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:17,600
What did the kiss feel like?

120
00:07:18,113 --> 00:07:20,813
Hey, are you going to stay up all night?

121
00:07:21,546 --> 00:07:24,046
What's going on? I thought she was asleep.

122
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:25,770
Did she hear everything we said?

123
00:07:25,843 --> 00:07:27,473
Don't worry, she's sleep-talking.

124
00:07:28,086 --> 00:07:30,219
She'll mumble like that for a bit
and then fall back into deep sleep.

125
00:07:44,745 --> 00:07:46,945
It really must be a lucky charm.

126
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:49,100
What do I do?

127
00:07:54,225 --> 00:07:55,825
Hey, get lost!

128
00:07:56,218 --> 00:07:57,220
Can't you hear us?

129
00:07:57,222 --> 00:07:59,656
Get out of our playground right now!

130
00:08:00,170 --> 00:08:03,233
My mom told me not to go anywhere...

131
00:08:03,419 --> 00:08:05,352
and to wait here.

132
00:08:05,632 --> 00:08:06,932
You little brat!

133
00:08:17,626 --> 00:08:19,193
Hey, what are you guys doing?

134
00:08:20,152 --> 00:08:21,952
Why are you bullying a little girl?

135
00:08:22,332 --> 00:08:24,432
She's not from our neighborhood.

136
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,633
This is our playground.

137
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:32,016
Whatever. Do you want to get in trouble?

138
00:08:43,119 --> 00:08:47,053
If I catch you bullying weaker kids again,
I won't let it slide!

139
00:08:50,533 --> 00:08:51,566
Are you okay?

140
00:08:52,972 --> 00:08:54,006
That must hurt.

141
00:09:23,673 --> 00:09:25,506
Do you live around here?

142
00:09:25,939 --> 00:09:28,873
No, I just come here sometimes
with my dad.

143
00:09:30,177 --> 00:09:33,100
My dad is building those apartments.

144
00:09:33,350 --> 00:09:36,606
Does your dad own those apartments?

145
00:09:36,846 --> 00:09:38,746
No, he's the chief architect.

146
00:09:39,936 --> 00:09:42,766
He plans everything before construction,

147
00:09:42,917 --> 00:09:44,933
creates the blueprints and models,

148
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:46,793
and takes responsibility
until the very end.

149
00:09:54,666 --> 00:09:56,966
Try putting this here.

150
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:07,466
What should we do?

151
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:10,600
It's okay. If it collapses,
we can just build it again.

152
00:10:12,667 --> 00:10:13,766
Here, try again.

153
00:10:17,599 --> 00:10:19,633
Gyeol. Han Gyeol.

154
00:10:23,285 --> 00:10:24,285
I have to go.

155
00:10:24,879 --> 00:10:27,946
It's my birthday today,
so my dad is throwing me a party.

156
00:10:28,819 --> 00:10:30,419
Happy birthday.

157
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:31,960
Thanks.

158
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:35,700
This is a lucky flag.

159
00:10:35,913 --> 00:10:38,579
You can play with it
while you wait for your mom.

160
00:10:42,043 --> 00:10:43,398
A lucky flag?

161
00:10:43,603 --> 00:10:46,426
Yeah, my dad made it.

162
00:10:46,692 --> 00:10:48,059
If you have this,

163
00:10:48,879 --> 00:10:51,545
even if you're alone, you won't be scared
and you'll feel brave.

164
00:10:53,059 --> 00:10:54,426
Give it back next time we meet.

165
00:10:55,140 --> 00:10:57,240
I come here every Saturday.

166
00:10:58,473 --> 00:11:01,440
Next time, I'll build you a house
with ice cream sticks.

167
00:11:01,872 --> 00:11:02,872
Bye.

168
00:11:11,859 --> 00:11:12,859
Han Gyeol?

169
00:11:28,153 --> 00:11:29,220
Why aren't you coming, Mom?

170
00:11:30,292 --> 00:11:32,792
Mom!

171
00:11:36,516 --> 00:11:37,963
Haven't you eaten yet?

172
00:11:37,990 --> 00:11:38,833
No.

173
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:41,466
Why did you bring all this
so early in the morning?

174
00:11:41,566 --> 00:11:44,367
I made dried pollock soup
for Eun Ae's hangover.

175
00:11:44,653 --> 00:11:47,620
She drank a lot with Cho Rong yesterday.

176
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:49,466
My goodness...

177
00:11:52,010 --> 00:11:53,200
Hi, Mrs. Park.

178
00:11:53,260 --> 00:11:54,996
Is your stomach okay?

179
00:11:55,372 --> 00:11:57,506
Sorry? Yes, of course.

180
00:11:57,620 --> 00:11:58,843
Right.

181
00:11:58,895 --> 00:12:02,739
You must've felt
like you were walking on cloud nine,

182
00:12:02,741 --> 00:12:04,816
so what's a little hangover?

183
00:12:05,496 --> 00:12:07,966
That boy, or senior, or whatever...

184
00:12:08,123 --> 00:12:11,201
grabbed your cheeks like this
and gave you a deep kiss...

185
00:12:11,203 --> 00:12:13,700
I think you had a dream!

186
00:12:14,333 --> 00:12:15,333
A dream?

187
00:12:15,906 --> 00:12:17,316
No way.

188
00:12:18,366 --> 00:12:20,966
I'm a very light sleeper.

189
00:12:22,210 --> 00:12:23,600
You should hurry up and go.

190
00:12:23,789 --> 00:12:25,233
Go give Cho Rong her hangover soup. Hurry!

191
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:28,667
What's wrong? Is the proposal a secret?

192
00:12:29,013 --> 00:12:32,433
What? A proposal?

193
00:12:32,583 --> 00:12:34,033
No, it's nothing.

194
00:12:34,286 --> 00:12:36,053
Hurry up and go already.

195
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:40,030
If two adults over 30 share a deep kiss,

196
00:12:40,032 --> 00:12:41,366
it's a done deal.

197
00:12:41,705 --> 00:12:43,266
Gosh, seriously.

198
00:12:44,032 --> 00:12:45,299
Hey, what's going on?

199
00:12:45,572 --> 00:12:47,172
Tell me everything.
Don't leave out a single detail!

200
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:48,933
My goodness.

201
00:12:50,133 --> 00:12:52,699
Getting investment and a boyfriend
all at once.

202
00:12:53,199 --> 00:12:54,199
Congratulations, sweetheart.

203
00:12:55,536 --> 00:12:56,666
What happened?

204
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:59,633
You said he was just a senior
you had a crush on.

205
00:12:59,776 --> 00:13:02,533
That's what I thought too,

206
00:13:02,663 --> 00:13:04,643
but apparently, he liked me all along.

207
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:05,900
All of a sudden?

208
00:13:06,055 --> 00:13:08,496
After five years of not showing it once?

209
00:13:08,516 --> 00:13:10,600
He was just being careful.

210
00:13:10,773 --> 00:13:12,773
He wanted to start
after we were properly settled.

211
00:13:13,416 --> 00:13:15,233
Now that the investment is confirmed...

212
00:13:15,399 --> 00:13:17,266
Bring him home this weekend.

213
00:13:17,770 --> 00:13:20,000
What, home? Our house?

214
00:13:20,203 --> 00:13:22,333
Are you planning to introduce him
at your wedding?

215
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:24,700
When did I say I was getting married?

216
00:13:24,743 --> 00:13:26,733
We just decided to date.

217
00:13:26,833 --> 00:13:30,300
You're 30. Are you dating someone
you won't even marry?

218
00:13:30,799 --> 00:13:33,832
We should check
if he's a decent guy first.

219
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,600
He's her senior from school.
They've worked together for five years.

220
00:13:37,833 --> 00:13:39,366
I'm sure he's a decent guy.

221
00:13:39,366 --> 00:13:40,517
I can't trust her.

222
00:13:40,517 --> 00:13:43,634
She's so naive,
she falls for anyone who likes her.

223
00:13:44,086 --> 00:13:45,919
Mom, I'm really hurt.

224
00:13:46,453 --> 00:13:48,186
What? What are you hurt about?

225
00:13:48,586 --> 00:13:50,433
You weren't like this
with Eun Hyeong and Eun Nim.

226
00:13:50,716 --> 00:13:52,766
You said okay right away
without even meeting Eun Hyeong's wife.

227
00:13:52,766 --> 00:13:54,033
Every time Eun Nim changed boyfriends...

228
00:13:54,033 --> 00:13:56,433
Do you think you're the same as them?

229
00:13:57,946 --> 00:14:01,146
We should invite
Eun Hyeong's family that day too.

230
00:14:01,673 --> 00:14:02,906
Even Eun Hyeong?

231
00:14:02,966 --> 00:14:03,933
(Golden Fried Rice Recipe)

232
00:14:15,939 --> 00:14:16,939
Hi, Mother.

233
00:14:18,052 --> 00:14:19,385
Yes, this weekend?

234
00:14:20,546 --> 00:14:22,812
Sure. He's Eun Ae's boyfriend,
so I should meet him too.

235
00:14:23,103 --> 00:14:25,533
What's Ji Seon's schedule this weekend?

236
00:14:25,633 --> 00:14:26,533
I'm not sure.

237
00:14:26,533 --> 00:14:28,900
I'll ask her later today
when she gets back from her flight.

238
00:14:29,353 --> 00:14:30,919
Make sure you come together this time.

239
00:14:31,653 --> 00:14:34,653
Also, when do
your full-time professor results come out?

240
00:14:35,066 --> 00:14:36,733
I'm not sure yet.

241
00:14:36,853 --> 00:14:38,586
I'll let you know when they come out.

242
00:14:39,618 --> 00:14:41,151
I have to feed Bit Na breakfast.

243
00:14:41,153 --> 00:14:42,620
I'll call you later. Bye.

244
00:14:44,566 --> 00:14:46,733
I'm all ready for kindergarten, Dad.

245
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,000
My daughter is all grown up.

246
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,633
You can do everything on your own now.
Sit down.

247
00:14:53,980 --> 00:14:55,313
Fried rice again?

248
00:14:57,905 --> 00:15:00,972
Sorry, I'm good at everything else,

249
00:15:01,573 --> 00:15:02,873
but my cooking just won't improve.

250
00:15:03,525 --> 00:15:04,659
But it'll be different today.

251
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:07,133
Last time, I messed up
the oyster sauce measurement.

252
00:15:07,885 --> 00:15:10,119
Socrates said,

253
00:15:10,632 --> 00:15:12,099
"Know thyself."

254
00:15:13,110 --> 00:15:16,666
Dad, you know yourself very well,

255
00:15:16,879 --> 00:15:17,913
so it's okay.

256
00:15:18,230 --> 00:15:19,766
Bit Na, you know,

257
00:15:19,766 --> 00:15:21,600
Socrates didn't actually say that first.

258
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:23,653
It was on a pillar of a temple
at Delphi in Greece...

259
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:26,943
No, just eat for now.

260
00:15:26,957 --> 00:15:27,990
If you're late, Mom will tell us off.
Hurry and eat.

261
00:15:27,992 --> 00:15:29,559
- Thank you for the meal.
- Sure.

262
00:15:31,763 --> 00:15:33,666
- What does he like?
- What?

263
00:15:33,850 --> 00:15:36,000
What does your senior like to eat?

264
00:15:36,237 --> 00:15:39,200
I should prepare something he likes.

265
00:15:39,330 --> 00:15:43,530
Right. She just wants
to treat your boyfriend well.

266
00:15:43,990 --> 00:15:45,200
Ask him today.

267
00:15:45,365 --> 00:15:47,116
What do you mean treat him well?

268
00:15:47,146 --> 00:15:49,280
I'm just going to see if he's any good.

269
00:15:50,012 --> 00:15:53,312
But how did such a big investment decision
happen so quickly?

270
00:15:54,090 --> 00:15:55,423
That's amazing.

271
00:15:55,425 --> 00:15:57,825
You never know until the money's
actually in your account.

272
00:15:58,572 --> 00:16:01,439
Don't get ahead of yourselves.
Just eat breakfast.

273
00:16:02,606 --> 00:16:03,640
Sure.

274
00:16:06,779 --> 00:16:08,400
Hey, where are you going?

275
00:16:15,266 --> 00:16:16,733
Seriously, I...

276
00:16:17,919 --> 00:16:19,586
Why are you acting like that
toward Eun Ae?

277
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:22,366
Yeah, you went a bit too far today.

278
00:16:22,552 --> 00:16:24,686
What? What did I do?

279
00:16:26,452 --> 00:16:28,519
I'm just saying you should be cautious.

280
00:16:35,513 --> 00:16:37,313
Why are you getting upset over this now?

281
00:16:38,212 --> 00:16:39,846
Grow up, Cho Eun Ae.

282
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:56,267
Why are you so early, Ji Hun?

283
00:16:56,739 --> 00:16:57,739
Right...

284
00:16:58,439 --> 00:17:00,400
I just woke up early today.

285
00:17:00,733 --> 00:17:04,533
Actually, I barely slept at all.

286
00:17:05,986 --> 00:17:08,520
By the way, are you free this weekend?

287
00:17:08,793 --> 00:17:10,460
This weekend? Why?

288
00:17:10,866 --> 00:17:14,033
My family found out.

289
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,900
That we're dating.

290
00:17:16,853 --> 00:17:19,319
My mom wants to invite you
over this weekend.

291
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:22,804
That's too bad.

292
00:17:22,806 --> 00:17:25,639
I have to go down to Wanpyeong today,

293
00:17:26,213 --> 00:17:27,846
so I probably won't be in Seoul
this weekend.

294
00:17:28,338 --> 00:17:31,072
So that's why you were packing.

295
00:17:32,733 --> 00:17:35,200
Ji Hun, what does your mother like?

296
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:36,560
Why do you ask?

297
00:17:36,906 --> 00:17:39,706
I want to send her a small gift with you.

298
00:17:40,879 --> 00:17:44,212
I'm trying to get on her good side,
so tell me.

299
00:17:44,432 --> 00:17:46,232
There's no need.

300
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:51,133
Well then, maybe a scarf or something.

301
00:17:51,460 --> 00:17:52,560
- A scarf?
- Yeah.

302
00:17:52,979 --> 00:17:54,912
Then I'll go to the department store now.

303
00:17:54,952 --> 00:17:56,119
Okay.

304
00:17:56,437 --> 00:17:58,071
Take your time.

305
00:17:58,358 --> 00:17:59,263
Okay.

306
00:17:59,436 --> 00:18:03,543
By the way, when will Kangsu Construction
make the final call?

307
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:06,766
Don't I need to go and explain
the program myself?

308
00:18:06,899 --> 00:18:08,699
There'll be a meeting soon.

309
00:18:09,126 --> 00:18:11,159
Make sure you come with me then.

310
00:18:11,546 --> 00:18:13,530
Okay, got it.

311
00:18:14,299 --> 00:18:15,666
I'll be back soon.

312
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:23,467
(Kangsu Construction)

313
00:18:23,467 --> 00:18:26,067
(Lucky Joy Tech Intellectual Property
and Acquisition Agreement)

314
00:18:33,433 --> 00:18:36,233
Smooth and quick. It's perfect.

315
00:18:38,233 --> 00:18:40,867
Then should I start work from next month?

316
00:18:40,867 --> 00:18:43,333
Of course, just as stated in the contract.

317
00:18:48,980 --> 00:18:50,113
You came alone again today?

318
00:18:50,667 --> 00:18:52,300
Yes, I'm the CEO.

319
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,733
She's in charge of development.

320
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:56,767
Of course, we co-developed it together.

321
00:18:57,267 --> 00:19:00,033
Are you sure that developer
agreed to this contract willingly?

322
00:19:00,673 --> 00:19:01,773
What are you saying?

323
00:19:02,153 --> 00:19:04,387
Of course she agreed.
Otherwise, she wouldn't have signed it.

324
00:19:04,733 --> 00:19:07,767
Why did your partner
so readily sell the company?

325
00:19:07,767 --> 00:19:09,067
It's not even a personal scouting clause.

326
00:19:09,067 --> 00:19:12,667
It's because of money.

327
00:19:13,633 --> 00:19:15,067
She has some circumstances,

328
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:18,967
so she's receiving the full sale amount.

329
00:19:18,967 --> 00:19:21,700
Then the acquisition payment
should go into her account.

330
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,367
But the bank account
is under your name, Mr. Han.

331
00:19:25,367 --> 00:19:27,300
That's a joint corporate account.

332
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:29,500
It's just under my name.

333
00:19:29,867 --> 00:19:31,833
Why worry about details like that?

334
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:32,933
They'll handle it themselves.

335
00:19:33,267 --> 00:19:34,200
All right.

336
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:43,533
With this, Lucky Joy Tech's Joy

337
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:45,200
now belongs to Kangsu Construction.

338
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,567
- Good work.
- I look forward to working with you, sir.

339
00:19:56,267 --> 00:19:57,833
What? Something bothering you?

340
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:04,600
Hello, Mother.

341
00:20:05,967 --> 00:20:07,000
Grandpa?

342
00:20:07,667 --> 00:20:08,767
Yes, I'll be there soon.

343
00:20:20,367 --> 00:20:21,433
Where did he go?

344
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,567
The person you are trying to call
is unavailable.

345
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:31,233
I hope his mother likes it.

346
00:20:35,133 --> 00:20:39,400
He said he was just going to his parents',
so why clear everything out?

347
00:20:44,047 --> 00:20:47,747
Lung cancer? Stage four?

348
00:20:48,253 --> 00:20:49,720
My goodness.

349
00:20:49,767 --> 00:20:51,576
Stage four means there's no hope...

350
00:20:53,300 --> 00:20:56,067
Then why did you come home?

351
00:20:56,533 --> 00:20:57,867
You should be getting surgery right away,

352
00:20:57,867 --> 00:21:00,133
or starting chemotherapy or radiation.

353
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:01,267
That's right, Grandpa.

354
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:04,067
There's targeted therapy these days too.

355
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:06,367
Why all the fuss?

356
00:21:07,660 --> 00:21:10,526
Do you want me to spend
what little time I have left

357
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:12,833
in a hospital bed?

358
00:21:13,633 --> 00:21:16,733
Father, medical technology in our country
is so advanced.

359
00:21:16,735 --> 00:21:18,568
Why are you giving up?

360
00:21:19,033 --> 00:21:20,700
I know my own body.

361
00:21:21,967 --> 00:21:25,000
Don't say another word about this.

362
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:26,467
Seriously...

363
00:21:28,933 --> 00:21:31,467
What's with Dr. Kim and Mr. Seo?

364
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,900
As his attending physician
and chief of staff,

365
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:36,233
how could you let this happen?

366
00:21:37,533 --> 00:21:38,533
I apologize.

367
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:40,840
Why get angry at him?

368
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,120
I skipped...

369
00:21:44,033 --> 00:21:47,333
my checkups last year
and the year before because I was busy.

370
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:50,100
Even so, how can it already be terminal

371
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,800
after missing just two years?

372
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:56,200
I heard cancer grows slowly
in the elderly.

373
00:21:56,567 --> 00:21:59,133
Father, please don't give up.

374
00:21:59,627 --> 00:22:02,494
If it's not possible here,
I'll look into hospitals abroad.

375
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:04,000
Enough.

376
00:22:05,586 --> 00:22:08,286
This is why I didn't want to tell you.

377
00:22:10,033 --> 00:22:12,833
Please get up. You need to rest.

378
00:22:12,833 --> 00:22:13,833
Yes.

379
00:22:14,593 --> 00:22:16,526
Mr. Seo, you can go home.

380
00:22:17,367 --> 00:22:20,100
You've had it tough today because of me.

381
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:22,800
Not at all. Please rest well, sir.

382
00:22:28,579 --> 00:22:30,879
My goodness,
why is everyone here at this hour?

383
00:22:32,127 --> 00:22:33,227
You're here too?

384
00:22:34,921 --> 00:22:35,921
Hello, Mother.

385
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,567
Mother?

386
00:22:38,833 --> 00:22:40,800
What are you doing here at this hour?

387
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:43,300
I heard the Chairman
was being discharged today,

388
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:45,933
so I brought some marinated crab
since he might not have an appetite.

389
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:48,467
It may not be as good as yours, though.

390
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,700
Mr. Seo, let's talk for a moment.

391
00:23:02,167 --> 00:23:04,667
Don't be too hard on the kids.

392
00:23:05,500 --> 00:23:08,667
They're just shocked and worried.

393
00:23:11,666 --> 00:23:13,166
I feel the same way.

394
00:23:14,626 --> 00:23:16,926
Even if there's a ten percent chance...

395
00:23:18,287 --> 00:23:20,887
No, even if it's one percent,
I want to hold on to it.

396
00:23:22,033 --> 00:23:25,933
If I start treatment,
I won't be able to do anything.

397
00:23:27,567 --> 00:23:28,734
Until the moment I die,

398
00:23:30,100 --> 00:23:32,700
I'll be soaked in harsh drugs
and radiation.

399
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:35,867
As long as I,

400
00:23:37,167 --> 00:23:40,267
Ko Kang Su, am alive,
I want to live on my own terms.

401
00:23:40,901 --> 00:23:42,067
Honey.

402
00:23:44,453 --> 00:23:47,487
I'll do everything
I couldn't do with you...

403
00:23:47,567 --> 00:23:48,567
because I was too busy.

404
00:23:50,333 --> 00:23:54,733
We'll go flower viewing every season
and eat delicious food.

405
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:57,067
I don't need any of that.

406
00:23:58,100 --> 00:24:00,133
I don't need anything
except you getting better.

407
00:24:02,867 --> 00:24:04,733
You're so beautiful...

408
00:24:06,267 --> 00:24:08,367
Yet I can't even remember
the last time I saw you smile.

409
00:24:09,965 --> 00:24:11,703
It's all my fault.

410
00:24:11,705 --> 00:24:15,005
No, it's not. Why would it be your fault?

411
00:24:16,633 --> 00:24:19,200
Honey, please stop talking
and take your medicine.

412
00:24:22,266 --> 00:24:24,433
How could you? If you knew the results,

413
00:24:25,867 --> 00:24:27,800
you should have told me first.

414
00:24:28,414 --> 00:24:31,481
It was the Chairman's decision.
He said he would tell you himself.

415
00:24:32,076 --> 00:24:35,831
Do you think I'm a joke
because my father treats you...

416
00:24:35,833 --> 00:24:37,767
like his right-hand man
and meets you privately?

417
00:24:38,767 --> 00:24:40,267
Do I look like a nobody to you?

418
00:24:40,267 --> 00:24:41,667
You're worked up, sir.

419
00:24:41,667 --> 00:24:42,667
How could I not be?

420
00:24:42,667 --> 00:24:44,600
My father has been given
a terminal diagnosis.

421
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,333
Mind your words. "Terminal?"

422
00:24:47,733 --> 00:24:49,700
If you have nothing more to say,
I'll take my leave.

423
00:24:50,133 --> 00:24:51,133
Hey, Seo Gwon Sik.

424
00:24:53,267 --> 00:24:54,633
You seem to be mistaken.

425
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:58,400
I'm the Chairman's secretary, not yours.

426
00:24:58,767 --> 00:25:01,433
What? What did you say?

427
00:25:01,867 --> 00:25:04,267
Hey, pick your side wisely.

428
00:25:04,933 --> 00:25:06,800
If you want to succeed,
get in the right line.

429
00:25:08,267 --> 00:25:11,967
Frankly speaking,
after my father passes away,

430
00:25:11,967 --> 00:25:13,733
who do you think will become
Chairman of Kangsu Group?

431
00:25:15,167 --> 00:25:16,767
Keep treating me like this,

432
00:25:16,767 --> 00:25:18,600
and I don't care if we go way back.
You're done.

433
00:25:28,467 --> 00:25:31,633
My goodness, poor Chairman.

434
00:25:32,346 --> 00:25:34,646
He's devoted his whole life
to Kangsu Group.

435
00:25:35,433 --> 00:25:37,267
If something goes wrong...

436
00:25:37,267 --> 00:25:40,900
What's the problem?
My husband will take over the company.

437
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:43,033
What? What do you mean?

438
00:25:43,713 --> 00:25:46,313
Are you saying the President
will become Chairman?

439
00:25:52,233 --> 00:25:53,267
Hello, Mrs. Kang.

440
00:25:54,867 --> 00:25:56,000
The second daughter of Samho Group?

441
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:59,007
Gosh, really?

442
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:03,620
I'll check my son's schedule
and contact you right away. Goodbye.

443
00:26:05,393 --> 00:26:07,993
Min Ho is going on a blind date
with the Samho Group's second daughter?

444
00:26:08,067 --> 00:26:10,167
You heard everything. Why are you asking?

445
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:15,207
I'm not sure if Min Ho will agree to it.

446
00:26:15,980 --> 00:26:17,280
What do you mean?

447
00:26:17,367 --> 00:26:20,167
Everybody knows that Min Ho...

448
00:26:20,167 --> 00:26:21,400
is devoted to Seung Ri.

449
00:26:22,321 --> 00:26:25,921
Sometimes, you really seem clueless.

450
00:26:25,967 --> 00:26:27,900
You don't seem to understand
how the world works.

451
00:26:28,367 --> 00:26:30,300
In families like ours,

452
00:26:30,300 --> 00:26:33,869
marriage is business
between families and corporations.

453
00:26:33,967 --> 00:26:35,834
How dare you even dread?

454
00:26:36,226 --> 00:26:38,893
You mean "dream," not "dread."

455
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:40,267
"How dare you even dream?"

456
00:26:40,267 --> 00:26:44,100
Whether it's "dream" or "dread,"
I majored in French literature.

457
00:26:44,706 --> 00:26:46,906
It's not a big deal if I get a word wrong.

458
00:26:48,033 --> 00:26:51,267
Right, French literature.

459
00:26:52,167 --> 00:26:53,600
De toute facon.

460
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:55,900
What? "Detou Fashion?"

461
00:26:55,900 --> 00:26:58,033
It means "anyway" in French.

462
00:26:59,100 --> 00:27:01,567
If you ever try to pair Min Ho
with Seung Ri again,

463
00:27:01,567 --> 00:27:03,967
don't even think about seeing me again,
got it?

464
00:27:04,186 --> 00:27:07,320
As if I came here just to see you.

465
00:27:08,333 --> 00:27:09,600
The phone is turned off.

466
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:12,067
After the tone,
you will be connected to...

467
00:27:13,066 --> 00:27:16,199
What on earth is going on?
Why can't I reach him at all?

468
00:27:17,006 --> 00:27:18,573
Could it be something bad?

469
00:27:19,256 --> 00:27:21,867
No, get a grip. Let's work.

470
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:28,667
(There is a problem with the server.)

471
00:27:29,267 --> 00:27:30,333
What? What's going on?

472
00:27:33,373 --> 00:27:35,407
This can't be happening.

473
00:27:38,433 --> 00:27:40,267
What is wrong with this?

474
00:27:49,720 --> 00:27:51,556
(We thank Baek Sung Hyun
for his special appearance.)

475
00:27:52,300 --> 00:27:54,867
(Our Happy Days)

476
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:56,900
Gyeol, you are coming back?

477
00:27:56,900 --> 00:27:58,167
The Chairman will be very happy.

478
00:27:58,167 --> 00:27:59,756
Is Gyeol coming back?

479
00:27:59,796 --> 00:28:01,733
The clock will start again,

480
00:28:01,733 --> 00:28:03,833
and so can we.

481
00:28:03,833 --> 00:28:06,600
Make sure you move out
by next weekend as promised.

482
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:08,300
What do you mean?

483
00:28:08,300 --> 00:28:10,100
You need to vacate the room.

484
00:28:10,100 --> 00:28:11,800
Nothing happened, right?

485
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:13,100
There's no way, right?

486
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:15,467
Where is Ji Hun? Where is he?

487
00:28:15,467 --> 00:28:16,900
Then what is this article?

488
00:28:16,900 --> 00:28:19,400
What happened? An acquisition?

489
00:28:20,100 --> 00:28:21,633
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
